data.text: Khoy County (Persian: شهرستان خوی‎) is a county in West Azerbaijan Province in Iran. At the 2006 census, the county's population (including those portions later split off to form Chaypareh County was 365,573, in 85,550 families; excluding those portions, the population was 323,348, in 75,464 families.
